EHS - Exclusive Hacking Services

EHS is a group of currently 5 professional hackers, all located in Europe. We provide an Exclusive Hacking Service for customers all over the world. If you need something to be hacked, you have just found the place to be. In 2016, a lot of .onion sites out there are scams. Before you proceed any further, make sure you understand the following statement.

ANY SERVICE THAT HAS A 100% SUCCESS RATE IS FAKE

Every case is unique and unless a hacker has hacked the exact same service before, it is impossible to provide you with a 100% success rate. However, we do our best to kick the success rate as high as possible. Below we have added a list of main categories of why people are contacting us. The success rate is based on the succeeded and failed cases we have finished before. Every type also has two prices. The first one is the total price for the hack. The second one is the price that should be paid before any hacks are executed. The total amount (so the price minus the price paid upfront) should be paid after we have provided you with proof of success.

* These hacks are done by social engineering and the success rate is correlated with the strength of the password of the victim.

So how does it work? First, decide the category of the case (together with the price). Next, send the needed BTC to our wallet (which can be found at the bottom of this page). When all of this is done, contact us via mail and provide us with the details of the case as well as the transaction id of the payment. It usually takes max up to 24 hours before we approve and open the case. Then one of our hackers starts immediately and will contact you via his mail so you stay up to date. More info? Send us a mail first and we will try to answer as fast as possible. Please don't send questions about categories that are already listed on this page before payment. Cases that have paid upfront will have a higher priority.

For better security, you can use our public key below to encrypt all the mails you will send to us. This way you can make sure that no one has access to the content. Note that although this is optional, it is strongly advised to use it!
